{
    "name": "Giant Worker Bee",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Giant Worker Bee",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Worker bees, exclusively female, exist to feed and defend a hive. They have no qualms about sacrificing their lives when confronting intruders in their territory. Worker bees can fight singly, in small groups, or in swarms of dozens. Giant worker bees inject a venom with their stings, but this venom is rarely dangerous except to people sensitive to it. Other worker bees have no stinger and only bite their enemies.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq026li"
                    },
                    "page": 80
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Giant Bee",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Hive Minds",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Bees communicate with each other using complex combinations of movement and pheromones. They can share detailed information, particularly related to food, water, and dangers. A queen bee doesn't have the ability to directly control members of her hive, but she guides the entire hive's activities and, when necessary, its relocation. Some druids have attempted to tap into this hive mind to control giant bee swarms, with limited success.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                                "alt": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq026li"
                            },
                            "page": 80
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "druids",
                            "alt": "druids",
                            "game-obj": "Classes",
                            "aonid": 6
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "Like their smaller counterparts, giant bees are highly territorial. Many types of giant bees construct hives in caves or abandoned buildings and are quick to attack creatures that they deem a threat to the single fertile queen, who almost never leaves the hive. Although most common in warm biomes with lots of vegetation, some giant bees live in arid or cold environments and are solitary rather than hive-dwelling.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #169: Kindled Magic pg. 80",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq026li"
                    },
                    "page": 80
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
